	<Title>
		Avoid swimmers&apos; itch: Watch where you swim
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Swimmer&apos;s itch, also known as cercarial dermatitis, is an itchy rash caused by certain parasites that normally live on waterfowl and freshwater snails. To reduce your risk of swimmer&apos;s itch, avoid swimming in fresh water lakes in summer heat or in areas where swimmer&apos;s itch is a known problem or where posted signs warn of contamination.&lt;/p&gt;
